  ],
  "paras": [
    {
      "n": "¶ 1",
      "text": "The town's little newspaper had grown famous almost overnight, thanks to an unlikely <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Acronym\" data-pos=\"N.\" data-hindi=\"संक्षिप्त शब्द (आद्याक्षर से बना)\" data-meaning=\"A word formed from the initial letters of other words — pehle akshar se bana naya shabd.\" data-example=\"NASA is an acronym for the National Aeronautics and Space Administration.\">Acronym</span>: T.O.W. — \"The Old Watch\" — a citizen group Meera had helped organize after the monastery story broke."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 2",
      "text": "What had begun as one article now seemed to <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Actuate\" data-pos=\"V.\" data-hindi=\"प्रेरित करना\" data-meaning=\"To motivate into action, or cause a mechanism to operate — kaam karne ke liye prerit karna.\" data-example=\"Fear of losing his job actuated him to work harder than ever.\">Actuate</span> something larger. People who had never spoken up before found the <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Acumen\" data-pos=\"N.\" data-hindi=\"सूझबूझ / कुशाग्रता\" data-meaning=\"The ability to make good judgements and quick decisions — sahi faisle jaldi lene ki kshamata.\" data-example=\"Her business acumen helped the startup grow within five years.\">Acumen</span> to question decisions their town council had made for years."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 3",
      "text": "One of those decisions had caused an <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Acute\" data-pos=\"Adj.\" data-hindi=\"गंभीर / तीव्र\" data-meaning=\"Severe or intense; also sharp perception — teevra ya bahut samajhdar.\" data-example=\"The patient was rushed to hospital with acute abdominal pain.\">Acute</span> water shortage in the eastern farms — a problem the council had quietly ignored for a decade. Meera was <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Adamant\" data-pos=\"Adj.\" data-hindi=\"अड़ियल / दृढ़\" data-meaning=\"Refusing to change one's mind despite pressure — apni baat par ada rehna.\" data-example=\"She remained adamant that she would not sign without changes.\">Adamant</span> that this story would not be buried like the last one."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 4",
      "text": "She filed a formal request for records, and the council clerk handed her a file with a single <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Addendum\" data-pos=\"N.\" data-hindi=\"परिशिष्ट\" data-meaning=\"Additional material added at the end of a document — ant mein joda gaya bhaag.\" data-example=\"The lawyer attached an addendum clarifying the payment terms.\">Addendum</span> stapled to the back — a page someone had clearly hoped no one would read."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 5",
      "text": "Meera was <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Adept\" data-pos=\"Adj.\" data-hindi=\"निपुण / प्रवीण\" data-meaning=\"Very skilled or proficient at something — kisi kaam mein bahut kushal.\" data-example=\"He was adept at solving even the most complex puzzles.\">Adept</span> at reading between the lines of dull municipal reports. She began to <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Adhere\" data-pos=\"V.\" data-hindi=\"पालन करना / चिपकना\" data-meaning=\"To stick firmly, or to follow a rule or practice — niyam ka paalan karna.\" data-example=\"All employees are expected to adhere to the code of conduct.\">Adhere</span> to a strict routine: mornings for interviews, evenings for documents, no exceptions."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 6",
      "text": "An old farmer named Tomas became her most loyal <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Adherent\" data-pos=\"N.\" data-hindi=\"अनुयायी / समर्थक\" data-meaning=\"A supporter of a party, cause, or belief — kisi vichar ka samarthak.\" data-example=\"The movement gained thousands of new adherents within a year.\">Adherent</span> — a man who had said his <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Adieu\" data-pos=\"N.\" data-hindi=\"विदाई\" data-meaning=\"A goodbye, especially a final one — antim vidai ka shabd.\" data-example=\"They bid a tearful adieu at the airport before her flight.\">Adieu</span> to city life decades ago but still believed the truth mattered more than comfort."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 7",
      "text": "Tomas's farmhouse sat <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Adjacent\" data-pos=\"Adj.\" data-hindi=\"समीपवर्ती / निकट\" data-meaning=\"Next to or adjoining something else — kisi cheez ke bilkul paas.\" data-example=\"The new library was built adjacent to the old town hall.\">Adjacent</span> to the very reservoir the council had drained without warning. He remembered the meeting where the decision was made — a meeting that had been quietly made to <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Adjourn\" data-pos=\"V.\" data-hindi=\"स्थगित करना\" data-meaning=\"To break off a meeting to resume it later — baithak ko baad ke liye rokna.\" data-example=\"The judge decided to adjourn the hearing until more evidence arrived.\">Adjourn</span> early, before anyone could object."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 8",
      "text": "When Meera confronted the council chairman, he tried to <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Admonish\" data-pos=\"V.\" data-hindi=\"फटकारना / चेतावनी देना\" data-meaning=\"To warn or reprimand firmly but not harshly — sakhti se chetavni dena.\" data-example=\"The teacher admonished the students for talking during the exam.\">Admonish</span> her for \"stirring up trouble,\" his office walls <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Adorn\" data-pos=\"V.\" data-hindi=\"सजाना\" data-meaning=\"To decorate or make something more beautiful — sundar banana.\" data-example=\"Fresh flowers adorned every table at the wedding reception.\">Adorn</span>ed with photographs of himself shaking hands with donors."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 9",
      "text": "He was <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Adroit\" data-pos=\"Adj.\" data-hindi=\"कुशल / निपुण\" data-meaning=\"Clever or skilful, especially with hands or mind — kushal upyog karne wala.\" data-example=\"The adroit negotiator satisfied both sides of the dispute.\">Adroit</span> with words, skilled at turning any question back on the asker, surrounded always by aides offering nothing but <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Adulation\" data-pos=\"N.\" data-hindi=\"अत्यधिक प्रशंसा / खुशामद\" data-meaning=\"Excessive, often insincere admiration or praise — zaroorat se zyada prashansa.\" data-example=\"The pop star was surrounded by fans showering him with adulation.\">Adulation</span> for his every decision."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 10",
      "text": "Documents later proved that a private company had helped <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Adulterate\" data-pos=\"V.\" data-hindi=\"मिलावट करना\" data-meaning=\"To make impure by adding another substance — milawat karna.\" data-example=\"The dairy was fined for using chemicals to adulterate the milk.\">Adulterate</span> the town's water reports, quietly changing numbers to hide the shortage the reservoir had caused."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 11",
      "text": "Meera's article did not accuse anyone directly — it simply chose to <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Adumbrate\" data-pos=\"V.\" data-hindi=\"संकेत देना / रूपरेखा बताना\" data-meaning=\"To represent something in outline, or foreshadow it vaguely — halka sanket dena.\" data-example=\"The opening chapter adumbrates the tragedy that unfolds later.\">Adumbrate</span> the pattern and let readers draw their own conclusions about the <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Adverse\" data-pos=\"Adj.\" data-hindi=\"प्रतिकूल / हानिकारक\" data-meaning=\"Harmful or unfavourable, preventing success — nuksaandayak paristhiti.\" data-example=\"The medicine was recalled after reports of adverse side effects.\">Adverse</span> effects on the farms."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 12",
      "text": "Tomas became an outspoken <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Advocate\" data-pos=\"N./V.\" data-hindi=\"पैरोकार / समर्थन करना\" data-meaning=\"A public supporter of a cause; or to publicly recommend it — samarthak, ya samarthan karna.\" data-example=\"She has long been an advocate for stricter environmental regulations.\">Advocate</span> for the farmers, standing before the council with data no one could dismiss. A journalist from the capital even sent an <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Aerial\" data-pos=\"Adj.\" data-hindi=\"हवाई / आकाशीय\" data-meaning=\"Existing or moving in the air — hawa mein hone wala.\" data-example=\"The photographer captured a stunning aerial view of the city.\">Aerial</span> photographer to document the dried-up fields from above."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 13",
      "text": "The photographs were not just accurate — they were oddly <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Aesthetic\" data-pos=\"Adj.\" data-hindi=\"सौंदर्यपरक\" data-meaning=\"Concerned with beauty or its appreciation — sundarta se sambandhit.\" data-example=\"The architect focused on aesthetic appeal as much as strength.\">Aesthetic</span>, cracked earth catching the evening light in a way that made the whole country pay attention."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 14",
      "text": "The new council candidate who emerged from the farmers' meetings was refreshingly <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Affable\" data-pos=\"Adj.\" data-hindi=\"मिलनसार / मृदुभाषी\" data-meaning=\"Friendly, good-natured, and easy to talk to — mridu swabhav wala.\" data-example=\"The affable shopkeeper greeted every customer with a warm smile.\">Affable</span>, someone with an obvious <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Affinity\" data-pos=\"N.\" data-hindi=\"स्वाभाविक आकर्षण / लगाव\" data-meaning=\"A natural liking or attraction to something — swabhavik lagav.\" data-example=\"She has always had a strong affinity for classical music.\">Affinity</span> for listening rather than lecturing."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 15",
      "text": "Officials tried to <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Affix\" data-pos=\"V.\" data-hindi=\"जोड़ना / चिपकाना\" data-meaning=\"To attach or fasten something to another object — jodna ya chipkana.\" data-example=\"Please affix a recent photograph to the application form.\">Affix</span> blame on a junior clerk, but the truth continued to <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Afflict\" data-pos=\"V.\" data-hindi=\"पीड़ित करना\" data-meaning=\"To cause pain, suffering, or distress — dukh pahunchana.\" data-example=\"The disease has afflicted thousands of farmers this year.\">Afflict</span> their carefully built reputation, no matter how <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Affluent\" data-pos=\"Adj.\" data-hindi=\"धनी / समृद्ध\" data-meaning=\"Having a great deal of money or wealth — bahut dhan-daulat wala.\" data-example=\"The affluent neighbourhood was known for its large gardens.\">Affluent</span> their defence lawyers were."
    },
    {
      "n": "¶ 16",
      "text": "In the <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Aftermath\" data-pos=\"N.\" data-hindi=\"परिणाम / दुष्परिणाम\" data-meaning=\"The consequences of a significant, usually unpleasant, event — ghatna ke baad ke parinaam.\" data-example=\"In the aftermath of the earthquake, thousands were left homeless.\">Aftermath</span> of the scandal, three council members resigned. A few loyalists tried to <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Aggravate\" data-pos=\"V.\" data-hindi=\"बढ़ाना / और बिगाड़ना\" data-meaning=\"To make a bad situation worse — samasya ko aur bigaad dena.\" data-example=\"Scratching the rash will only aggravate the irritation further.\">Aggravate</span> tensions by blaming the press — but the <span class=\"vw\" data-word=\"Aggregate\" data-pos=\"N./Adj.\" data-hindi=\"कुल योग / सम्मिलित\" data-meaning=\"A whole formed by combining several elements, as a total — alag hisson ka kul yog.\" data-example=\"The aggregate score of all three rounds decided the winner.\">Aggregate</span> result of the whole affair was a town that finally trusted its own water reports again."
    }
  ]
}